Source: hscolour
Priority: optional
Section: haskell
Maintainer: Debian Haskell Group <pkg-haskell-maintainers@lists.alioth.debian.org>
Uploaders: Erik de Castro Lopo <erikd@mega-nerd.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 5.0.0),ghc6 (>= 6.10.3-3), ghc6-prof, cdbs,
 haskell-devscripts (>= 0.6.15+nmu12)
Build-Depends-Indep: haddock, ghc6-doc
Standards-Version: 3.8.2
Homepage: http://hackage.haskell.org/cgi-bin/hackage-scripts/package/hscolour

Package: hscolour
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Haskell program to colourise Haskell code
 .
 HsColour currently has five output formats: ANSI terminal codes, HTML 3.2
 with <font> tags, HTML 4.01 with CSS, LaTeX, and mIRC chat client
 codes.

Package: libghc6-hscolour-dev
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${haskell:Depends}
Suggests: hscolour-doc (= ${source:Version}), hscolour (= ${binary:Version}),
 drift (>= 2.2.0)
Description: GHC6 libraries for colourising Haskell code
 .
 HsColour currently has five output formats: ANSI terminal codes, HTML 3.2
 with <font> tags, HTML 4.01 with CSS, LaTeX, and mIRC chat client
 codes.
 .
 This package contains the libraries compiled for GHC 6.

Package: libghc6-hscolour-prof
Architecture: any
Depends: libghc6-hscolour-dev (= ${binary:Version}), ${haskell:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends}
Suggests: hscolour-doc (= ${source:Version})
Description: Profiling libraries for colourising Haskell code
 .
 HsColour currently has five output formats: ANSI terminal codes, HTML 3.2
 with <font> tags, HTML 4.01 with CSS, LaTeX, and mIRC chat client
 codes.
 .
 This package contains the profiling libraries compiled for GHC 6.

Package: libghc6-hscolour-doc
Architecture: all
Section: doc
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: doc-base, libghc6-base-doc
Description: Documentation for libghc6-hscolour-dev
 .
 HsColour currently has five output formats: ANSI terminal codes, HTML 3.2
 with <font> tags, HTML 4.01 with CSS, LaTeX, and mIRC chat client
 codes.
 .
 This package contains the library documentation.
